The paper deals with the stability analysis of a slotted-Aloha system, which is a classic problem in information theory and networking. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category. The paper also involves the analysis of a shared resource/channel, which is a common theme in networking and communication systems, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) another likely category. The paper also discusses the stability of the system, which is a control theory problem, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category. The paper also involves the use of Markovian processes, which is a topic in probability theory, making cs.PF (Probability) another possible category. Finally, the paper involves numerical experiments and theoretical analysis, which are topics in computational mathematics, making cs.MA (Mathematical Software) a possible category.
